modules.description: This module handles serialization and deserialization of GitHub analytics data (users, issues, commits, releases) stored in key-value maps, supporting both string-indexed (`Smap`) and integer-indexed (`Imap`) structures. It enables asynchronous persistence to disk via Lwt-based `store` operations, allowing efficient loading and saving of database snapshots. Typical use cases involve caching GitHub repository metrics or maintaining versioned backups of tracked entities.

This module provides serialization and disk persistence for GitHub analytics data using key-value maps, with support for string and integer keys. It offers `Smap` and `Imap` types for structured data storage and Lwt-based `store` operations for asynchronous loading and saving of database snapshots. You can use it to cache repository metrics, track entity changes over time, or maintain versioned backups of users, issues, commits, and releases.
